Cell Quality Effects

I am testing the quality effects, since it could be a source of error and potentially biased the predicted gwRR if some mice had bad technical noise.

The the plots below, each point is a single mouse’s mean MLH1 count per cell across each quality score bin.

These plots show that generally there is a positive relationship between good quality (1) and more MLH1 counts.

I should focus on addressing if there are differences in the relationship of quality-MLH1 counts across sexes.

Age Effect (male)

Some papers have documented age effects for male genome-wide recombination rate [@zelazowski2017age].

The initial analysis uses plots. This should be double checked with a general linear model as well.

I made 3 models for 3 groupings of mice, dom, musc.high and musc.low

\[mouse .mean CO ~=~ age + strain + \varepsilon\]

ADD euthdate?

Dom, no significant effects for age.

Musc low, no significant effect for strain or age.

Musc high, MSM and SKIVE have significant age effects on mean CO count

SKIVE has the greatest spread in ages for single mice (7,16,41 weeks) There are more SKIVE males which I haven’t quantified (at least 3, which are in a good age range)

I like this plot and find it effective. Can I do a similar set up for other factors (quality, ncells?)

While many slopes are different than 0, I am not convinced there is a clear age effect. Most strains don’t have more than 2 ages. I will double check some of these mice and check a general linear model.

Room effect

When this project was started the main mouse room for vendor purchased mice was Biotech. The mouse room changed in summer 2017. The Gough mice were always housed in Charmony. Of the final dataset there are three strains had mice housed in different rooms; WSB, LEW, and MSM.

The main questions to address in this section: is there a significant GxE effect due to room? do the different rooms added noise / bias the estimates per strain

A room effect might cause all of the strains to be biased in the same direction.

Looking at my records, there are limited comparisons (not all strains were raised in all 3 rooms).

WSB female - Biotech vs Charmony

LEW female and male, MSM female and male - Biotech and MSC
